own additions:
- added dmenu_run_custom script
    - includes .desktop files from .local/share/applications/ and /usr/share/
        - will take a little longer on first run to cache entries
        - after initial caching will update on change (fast)
    - includes aliases from .config/dmenu_custom/aliases
        - syntax: alias <name>=<command>
            - don't use quotes!
    

dmenu - dynamic menu
====================
dmenu is an efficient dynamic menu for X.


Requirements
------------
In order to build dmenu you need the Xlib header files.


Installation
------------
Edit config.mk to match your local setup (dmenu is installed into
the /usr namespace by default).

Afterwards enter the following command to build and install dmenu
(if necessary as root):

    make clean install


Running dmenu
-------------
See the man page for details.
